Gerais (Juiz de Fora, Viçosa, Muriaé, Manhumirim and Urucânia), with different
territorial sizes according to the parameters of the Brazilian Institute of Geography and
Statistics (IBGS). This is a qualitative research that used as tools for data collection
the participant observation method and semi structured interviews. The results suggest
