carried out was interrupted and resumed at various times. At the beginning of 2018, after a
period of one year of work stoppage, the work was restarted with a view to its conclusion.
This research deals with the elaboration process of the PDDI of Metropolitan Region of the
Steel Valley (RMVA), considering its relevance for the planning, management and execution
of public functions of common interest, until its standstill. For this, this research was
organized in articles format, allowing the evaluation of the various urban development
instruments that will be adopted by the RMVA, from the conclusion of the PDDI. The
research begins with the evaluation of inter-financial governance, defined by the legal
framework that established RMVA. The PDDI Diagnosis is then evaluated, to understand the
characteristics of the municipalities that integrate the RMVA. An evaluation is made of the
